parameters:
Chancellor: How disgraceful. What happened to your vaunted
swordsmanship, Reisha?

I can't... I simply cannot... raise my sword against someone
I have sworn loyalty to...

Chancellor: Hahahahahaha!!! Excellent! Even now, you choose
the way of the knight over your own life?!

Chancellor: Kuhahahaha!! This is truly amusing! I'll admit
it, you are the finest knight in this kingdom!! And the most
foolish one at that!!

My lord, I ask you once more. Please, awaken. You should not
desire such things...

Be strong of heart...!! The power you wish to wield should
not be like this...!!!

Chancellor: Is this your knightly pretense until the very
end? Has it granted you anything? What have you gained at
the end of this journey you were led on?

Chancellor: Unable to obtain the holy sword, unable to
protect what's important, only increasing the number of
wounds on your body, and comforting yourself with the notion
of chivalry?

Chancellor: You have achieved nothing and ended in vain. At
the end of your journey, everything was for naught, Reisha.

Chancellor: As a final tribute, die in tragedy like a
knight. Perhaps someone will shed tears for you.
????: Reisha, your journey wasn't a waste.

????: Come on, stand tall as you always do, and show me
those eyes that look straight ahead.
Akane: Yo! Reisha! That was a close call, huh...!

Chancellor: Who the hell are you!!! How did you get in
here??
Akane: How? I just desperately followed this guy's shadow.

Akane: Well, it was easy to sneak in since it looked like a
tornado had cleared out all the small fry.

Akane: The royal chancellor would be appalled. With security
like this, it's like you're inviting burglars in.

Chancellor: Hmph, if you think adding one more thief to the
mix will change the situation, you're sorely mistaken.

Chancellor: It's just one more piece of fodder for the
king's blood. Along with all the other naive knights here.
Akane: Yeah, I think so too.

Akane: Immature, ignorant of the world, and always going on
about knights and chivalry—it gets under your skin.

Akane: ...But there are those who have been saved by that
naivety.

Akane: That's why I dream of a knight who still sheds blood
for someone else's sake.

Akane: Because that naivety, that conviction is within her!
That's why I'm here, and why this sword is here!

Akane: I won't let anyone deny her feelings. Especially not
scumbags like you!!

Chancellor: Tch! A mere thief...! Speaking as if you know
everything!!

Akane: Reisha. It took me a bit to find the sword you lost,
but I made it just in time.

Akane: Now take up your sword. Show me your proud stance as
always.

Akane: You did well on your own. Don't worry, from here on
out, I'll fight alongside you.

Akane: Hey hey, what's with that face? Aren't you a splendid
knight? Pull yourself together, come on!!

Akane: I'll listen to all your complaints and words of
thanks after everything's over. So before that, regrasp your
sword for the sake of what you truly want to protect.

The one I wanted to protect... The one I wanted to save...
But I cannot bring myself to raise my sword against my own
lord...

Akane: You're not swinging your sword to hurt your lord!
You're doing it to save your lord!!

Akane: What you really need to protect isn't your pride! It
should be the precious person right in front of you!!!

Akane: Because you have the desire to save her from her
suffering, that's why there's a sword in your hand, isn't
it?!
What I truly should protect, huh...

To think that I would be taught by you. I still have a long
way to go.

(In the midst of the tragedy that swept through, there were
indeed those I couldn't save...)

(Then at least let me carry on her will. The will of the one
who lived her life for others in the darkness.)

(The will of those who desperately struggled to protect
whatever was within their reach.)

By some twist of fate, this sword has returned to my hands,
the sword of beginnings...!!

Akane: That's right, those eyes! You're starting to look
like yourself again!!

Chancellor: Even if you can fight again, it doesn't change
the situation. Before the infinite magic power, everything
will turn to dust!!!

Chancellor: Don't get ahead of yourself. The sword in your
hands is not the legendary holy sword.

Akane: That's where you're wrong. The legendary sword is
what ends up in the hands of the last one standing.

Akane: Even if it's just an ordinary iron sword found
anywhere!
Akane: I prefer it that way! No, that's definitely better!!

(I can feel a certain power from within this sword. A quiet
strength that has absorbed the magical energy filling that
cave.)
Would you like to start the battle?

"Sword of Waterfall Sound" is not equipped. Would you still
like to start the battle?
Akane: Then this is round two! Don't hold me back!
Yes! And don't you hold me back either!!!
